        "jsonBody": "={{ JSON.stringify({ model: \"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\", max_tokens: 400, temperature: 0.4, messages: [ { role: \"system\", content: \"You are a matching engine. You receive a user profile and a list of government schemes with eligibility criteria. For each scheme, check EVERY field individually and explicitly before deciding: age range, income cap (the user's income must be LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO the cap), occupation, state, caste category, gender, and disability requirement. A user must satisfy ALL fields to be eligible — do not describe a criterion as 'met' unless you have explicitly verified the number or value against the scheme's requirement. A match on some fields does not override a mismatch on others. Return only schemes the user is eligible for, ranked by relevance, in warm plain conversational language (not JSON), under 150 words, bolding scheme names. Only mention schemes explicitly listed above — never invent scheme names. If no schemes match, say so clearly. For each matched scheme, also tell the user how to apply, including the application link if available.\" }, { role: \"user\", content: \"User profile: \" + JSON.stringify($('ParseAgentResponse').item.json.profile) + \"\\n\\nSchemes: \" + JSON.stringify($json.schemes) } ] }) }}",
